{
  "texts": [
    "This can help accelerate the development of LLMs tailored to specific needs.",
    "Thirdly, if researchers have access to low-cost computing resources, they can leverage open-source models for their work without incurring financial costs.",
    "Fourthly, open-source models that are operated locally offer significant privacy benefits as sensitive data does not need to be channeled over the internet to be processed on the servers of proprietary model providers.",
    "Finally, open-source models allow for greater reproducibility, which is helpful for ensuring scientific integrity in research as it enables other researchers to verify and build upon the reported results.",
    "These benefits make open-source language models an attractive choice for natural language processing."
  ]
}